  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(7) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For the sons of Athaliah.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—There is nothing corresponding to the statements of this verse in the parallel account. Literally, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For Athaliah, the evildoer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (or, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "who did wickedly,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 20:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "her sons had broken down",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 5:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 80:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the house of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Ahaziah and his elder brothers, and perhaps other relatives, may be intended. The young princes thus gratified the queen’s hatred of the exclusive ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cultus",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of Jehovah. (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Chronicles 22:3-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) Perhaps some portions of the Temple buildings were demolished, in order to make room for the temple of Baal. (Comp. Notes on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2Kings 11:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The dedicated things—i.e., the moneys given for the use of the sanctuary.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The dedicated things",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " the moneys given for the use of the sanctuary.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Did they bestow upon Baalim.—Or, they made into the Baals, i.e., used them in making idolatrous images and symbols. (Comp. the same expression, Hosea 2:8 : “Her silver and gold, which they made into Baal;” comp. also Hosea 8:4.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Did they bestow upon Baalim.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Or, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "they made into the Baals, i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " used them in making idolatrous images and symbols. (Comp. the same expression, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hosea 2:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " : “Her silver and gold, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "which they made into Baal;",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "” comp. also ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Hosea 8:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
